### Manual Test Guide for Prompts
### 1. Run the BasicServer: `dotnet run --project examples/BasicServer`
### 2. Use this file with the "REST Client" extension in VS Code.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

### 1. List All Prompts
POST {{baseUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "prompts/list",
  "params": {},
  "id": 1
}

### 2. Get 'analyze_code' Prompt (No arguments - uses defaults)
POST {{baseUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "prompts/get",
  "params": {
    "name": "analyze_code"
  },
  "id": 2
}

### 3. Get 'analyze_code' Prompt (With arguments)
POST {{baseUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "prompts/get",
  "params": {
    "name": "analyze_code",
    "arguments": {
      "code": "Console.WriteLine(\"Hello Manual Test\");",
      "language": "csharp"
    }
  },
  "id": 3
}

### 4. Get 'generate_test' Prompt
POST {{baseUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "prompts/get",
  "params": {
    "name": "generate_test",
    "arguments": {
        "functionName": "CalculateTax",
        "requirements": "Input: 100, Rate: 0.1 -> Output: 10"
    }
  },
  "id": 4
}
